Sleep is for the week, Mr. President

158
00:13:11,377 --> 00:13:12,779
Mr. President

159
00:13:12,912 --> 00:13:14,647
CIA's been notified

160
00:13:14,814 --> 00:13:17,083
McCone's on his way back
from the West coast

161
00:13:17,183 --> 00:13:19,219
He's been burying his step-son

162
00:13:19,285 --> 00:13:20,887
General Carter's here, though

163
00:13:24,090 --> 00:13:25,091
Ted

164
00:13:25,158 --> 00:13:26,526
Kenny

165
00:13:27,126 --> 00:13:28,728
Okay

166
00:13:31,197 --> 00:13:32,599
Let's have it

167
00:13:33,099 --> 00:13:34,367
Arthur?

168
00:13:34,767 --> 00:13:36,336
Gentlemen, as most of you now know

169
00:13:36,436 --> 00:13:39,305
a U-2 over Cuba

170
00:13:39,405 --> 00:13:41,841
Sunday morning took
a series of disturbing photographs

171
00:13:41,908 --> 00:13:43,810
Our analysis at NPIC indicates
that the Soviet Union

172
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:48,448
has followed up its conventional
weapons build-up in Cuba

173
00:13:48,548 --> 00:13:49,215
with the introduction of

174
00:13:49,282 --> 00:13:55,421
surface- to-surface medium range
ballistic missiles, or MRBM's

175
00:13:55,488 --> 00:13:58,858
Our official estimate at this time
is that this missiles system

176
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:01,828
is the SS-4 Sandal

177
00:14:01,961 --> 00:14:04,597
We do not believe that

178
00:14:04,731 --> 00:14:06,065
the missiles are as yet operational

179
00:14:06,199 --> 00:14:09,502
IRONBARK reports that the SS-4

180
00:14:09,569 --> 00:14:12,071
can deliver a 3-megaton
nuclear weapon 1, 000 miles

181
00:14:12,172 --> 00:14:14,641
So far we've identified 32 missiles
serviced by about 3, 400 men

182
00:14:14,774 --> 00:14:19,879
undoubtedly all Soviet personnel

183
00:14:20,046 --> 00:14:22,782
Our cities and military installations
in the southeast

184
00:14:22,816 --> 00:14:25,218
as far north as Washington, D. C.

185
00:14:25,285 --> 00:14:27,687
are in range of these weapons

186
00:14:27,787 --> 00:14:30,890
and in the event of a launch would
have only five minutes of warning

187
00:14:30,990 --> 00:14:32,392
Five minutes, gentlemen

188
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:33,660
In those five minutes

189
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:36,563
they could kill 80 million Americans

190
00:14:36,596 --> 00:14:42,235
and destroy a significant
percentage of our bomber bases

191
00:14:43,803 --> 00:14:46,272
The Joint Chiefs' consensus
Mr. President

192
00:14:46,339 --> 00:14:50,009
is that this signals a major
doctrinal shift in Soviet thinking

193
00:14:50,076 --> 00:14:52,846
to a first-strike policy

194
00:14:52,946 --> 00:14:56,182
It is a massively destabilizing move

195
00:14:56,282 --> 00:14:58,084
How long until they're operational?

196
00:14:58,184 --> 00:15:00,787
General Taylor can answer
that question better than I can

197
00:15:00,954 --> 00:15:03,423
GMAIC- Guided Missiles
Intelligence Committee

198
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:06,159
estimates ten to fourteen days

199
00:15:07,093 --> 00:15:09,395
A crash program could limit that time

200
00:15:09,529 --> 00:15:13,199
However, I must stress that
there may be more missiles

201
00:15:13,299 --> 00:15:15,034
that we don't know about

202
00:15:15,468 --> 00:15:17,504
We need more U-2 coverage

203
00:15:17,570 --> 00:15:19,572
Gentlemen, I want first reactions here

204
00:15:19,639 --> 00:15:21,307
Assuming for the moment that Krushev
has not gone off the deep end

205
00:15:21,407 --> 00:15:23,710
and intends to start World War Three

206
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:25,111
What are we looking for?

207
00:15:25,245 --> 00:15:28,848
Mr. President, My team is in agreement

208
00:15:28,915 --> 00:15:31,117
If we permit
the introduction of nuclear missiles

209
00:15:31,184 --> 00:15:34,154
to a Soviet satellite nation
in our hemisphere

210
00:15:34,254 --> 00:15:38,925
the diplomatic consequences
will be too terrible to contemplate

211
00:15:38,992 --> 00:15:42,028
The Russians are trying to show the
world they can do whatever they want

212
00:15:42,095 --> 00:15:43,496
wherever they want
and we're powerless to stop them

213
00:15:43,596 --> 00:15:44,531
If they succeed

214
00:15:44,597 --> 00:15:46,466
It'll be Munich all over again

215
00:15:46,566 --> 00:15:50,036
Yes. Appeasement only makes
the aggressor more aggressive

216
00:15:50,136 --> 00:15:52,839
And the Soviets will be
emboldened to push us even harder

217
00:15:52,906 --> 00:15:55,775
No, we must remove the missiles
one way or another

218
00:15:55,909 --> 00:15:57,810
It seems to me the options are either

219
00:15:57,977 --> 00:15:59,445
some combination of
international pressure

220
00:15:59,546 --> 00:16:02,649
and action on our part
till they give up

221
00:16:02,782 --> 00:16:04,617
or...

222
00:16:04,751 --> 00:16:06,352
we hit them

223
00:16:06,452 --> 00:16:08,354
An air strike

224
00:16:08,488 --> 00:16:09,589
Bob?

225
00:16:09,722 --> 00:16:12,158
We've worked up
several military scenarios

226
00:16:12,292 --> 00:16:14,761
Before I ask General Taylor to
take us through the various options

227
00:16:14,828 --> 00:16:16,796
I'd like for us to adopt a rule

228
00:16:16,930 --> 00:16:19,032
If we strike

229
00:16:19,132 --> 00:16:23,570
we must agree to do it before
the missiles become operational

230
00:16:23,636 --> 00:16:26,573
Because once they are

231
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:28,641
I don't think we can guarantee

232
00:16:28,775 --> 00:16:30,844
getting them all before
at least some of them are launched

233
00:16:32,278 --> 00:16:33,146
It's clear

234
00:16:33,279 --> 00:16:35,982
we cannot permit Soviet
nuclear missiles in Cuba

235
00:16:41,921 --> 00:16:44,424
We have to get those missiles out

236
00:16:45,391 --> 00:16:48,761
I don't think it's going to matter
what Kruschev's intentions are

237
00:16:49,629 --> 00:16:50,430
Right now

238
00:16:50,497 --> 00:16:53,633
I don't see any way
around hitting them

239
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,301
If we kill a lot of Russians

240
00:16:55,435 --> 00:16:56,903
they'll move against Berlin

241
00:16:57,003 --> 00:17:00,340
If they attack Berlin, that's NATO

242
00:17:00,406 --> 00:17:01,641
and we're at war

243
00:17:01,741 --> 00:17:03,176
We're damned if we do, but if we don't

244
00:17:03,309 --> 00:17:04,644
we're in a war for sure
somewhere else in six months

245
00:17:04,711 --> 00:17:06,179
If there are alternatives
that make sense

246
00:17:06,246 --> 00:17:08,248
and I'm not saying that there are

247
00:17:08,348 --> 00:17:09,682
then we need 'em, and fast

248
00:17:09,816 --> 00:17:11,784
What about Congress?

249
00:17:11,885 --> 00:17:13,753
We may need to
start letting key people know

250
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,688
And they're all scattered
across the country for the campaign

251
00:17:15,788 --> 00:17:16,689
We can get Congress back

252
00:17:16,756 --> 00:17:19,359
We're gonna need to
get the U. N. staff in and warmed up

253
00:17:19,425 --> 00:17:20,527
What about the allies?

254
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:22,395
We can't start
worrying about everything

255
00:17:22,495 --> 00:17:23,463
Right now we gotta figure out
what we're gonna do

256
00:17:23,596 --> 00:17:25,331
before we worry about
how we're gonna do it

257
00:17:25,431 --> 00:17:27,367
Well, we've got a bunch of smart guys

258
00:17:27,433 --> 00:17:29,669
We lock 'em in a room
and kick 'em in the ass

259
00:17:29,736 --> 00:17:32,205
until they come up
with some solutions

260
00:17:33,973 --> 00:17:35,708
I'll do it

261
00:17:37,844 --> 00:17:40,380
It's too politicized with you
in there anyway

262
00:17:40,446 --> 00:17:42,048
They need to be able to
stick their necks out

263
00:17:42,148 --> 00:17:43,516
Yeah. It'll be the principals

264
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:46,286
a couple of they key guys
from each department

265
00:17:46,386 --> 00:17:49,823
The Executive Committee
of the National Security Council

266
00:17:49,923 --> 00:17:52,592
We'll can it EXCOM

267
00:17:52,725 --> 00:17:54,093
Okay

268
00:17:54,194 --> 00:17:57,397
So I'm only gonna show
for the meetings that you call me into

269
00:17:57,530 --> 00:17:59,132
Impress us

270
00:17:59,265 --> 00:18:01,134
Did it fast

271
