Mr. Secretary

1592
01:30:48,935 --> 01:30:51,371
We're very busy right now
We need to able to do our job

1593
01:30:51,504 --> 01:30:54,874
Admiral! I asked you a question

1594
01:30:54,974 --> 01:30:57,944
We're going to
follow the rules of engagement

1595
01:30:58,044 --> 01:31:01,848
The rules of engagement
which the President

1596
01:31:01,915 --> 01:31:03,616
has approved and signed
in his order of 23 October

1597
01:31:04,751 --> 01:31:06,519
Yes

1598
01:31:07,120 --> 01:31:09,022
You may proceed, Captain

1599
01:31:09,189 --> 01:31:10,490
Cler your guns

1600
01:31:13,860 --> 01:31:14,794
Dammit!

1601
01:31:14,928 --> 01:31:15,628
Stop that firing!

1602
01:31:15,762 --> 01:31:16,129
What?

1603
01:31:16,196 --> 01:31:18,298
Stop that firing!

1604
01:31:18,364 --> 01:31:20,266
Cease fire

1605
01:31:20,366 --> 01:31:21,835
God help us

1606
01:31:24,337 --> 01:31:26,239
That ship was firing starshells!

1607
01:31:26,372 --> 01:31:28,875
Starshells -- Flares, Mr. Secretary!

1608
01:31:28,942 --> 01:31:31,144
Goddammit, I've got a job to do here!

1609
01:31:31,244 --> 01:31:33,380
You've been camped out up there
since Monday night

1610
01:31:33,513 --> 01:31:36,649
You're exhausted
you're making mistakes

1611
01:31:36,750 --> 01:31:38,918
You interfere with me and
you will get some of my men killed

1612
01:31:38,985 --> 01:31:41,354
and I will not allow that!

1613
01:31:41,454 --> 01:31:43,056
Starshells

1614
01:31:43,156 --> 01:31:45,658
Get out of our way, Mr. Secretart!

1615
01:31:45,692 --> 01:31:47,394
The navy's been running blockades...

1616
01:31:47,494 --> 01:31:49,028
since the days of John Paul Jones!

1617
01:31:49,095 --> 01:31:50,597
I believe the President
made it clear that there will be...

1618
01:31:50,730 --> 01:31:53,666
no firing on ships
without his express permission

1619
01:31:53,800 --> 01:31:56,369
With all due respect, Mr. Secretary

1620
01:31:56,436 --> 01:31:58,371
we were not firing on that ship

1621
01:31:58,438 --> 01:31:59,472
What was that?

1622
01:31:59,572 --> 01:32:01,674
Firing on a ship
means attacking a ship!

1623
01:32:01,775 --> 01:32:03,910
We were not attacking that ship!

1624
01:32:04,010 --> 01:32:05,678
We were firing over it!

1625
01:32:05,779 --> 01:32:09,049
That was not the President's intention
when he gave that order

1626
01:32:09,149 --> 01:32:11,117
What if the Soviets
don't see the distinction?

1627
01:32:11,284 --> 01:32:14,654
What if they make the same mistake
I just made?

1628
01:32:14,788 --> 01:32:15,922
There will be no firing anything
near any Soviet ships

1629
01:32:16,022 --> 01:32:19,192
without my express permission!

1630
01:32:19,292 --> 01:32:22,162
Is that understood, Admiral?

1631
01:32:22,595 --> 01:32:24,497
Is it?

1632
01:32:25,799 --> 01:32:27,233
Yes, sir

1633
01:32:27,300 --> 01:32:29,069
And I will only
issue such instructions...

1634
01:32:29,202 --> 01:32:32,072
when ordered to by the President!

1635
01:32:33,673 --> 01:32:36,076
John Paul Jones!

1636
01:32:36,609 --> 01:32:38,978
You don't understand a thing
do you, Admiral?

1637
01:32:39,045 --> 01:32:41,047
This is not a blockade!

1638
01:32:41,147 --> 01:32:43,583
This is language!

1639
01:32:43,650 --> 01:32:46,720
A new vocabulary, the likes of
which the world has never seen!

1640
01:32:46,820 --> 01:32:51,458
This is President Kennedy
communicating with Secretary Krushcev

1641
01:32:59,065 --> 01:33:03,369
(Atlas Missile Launch Vandenberg, AFB)

1642
01:33:03,503 --> 01:33:05,472
Who the hell
authorized this missile test?

1643
01:33:05,572 --> 01:33:06,639
Who do you think?

1644
01:33:06,773 --> 01:33:08,908
God knows what this is
gonna communicate to the Soviets

1645
01:33:09,008 --> 01:33:11,077
Communicate with the Soviets?

1646
01:33:11,144 --> 01:33:12,746
We can't communitcate
with the Pentagon

1647
01:33:12,779 --> 01:33:15,081
and it's just across the goddam river

1648
01:33:15,148 --> 01:33:17,317
LaMay must think you're afraid of him

1649
01:33:17,417 --> 01:33:19,452
I'm not taking that biat

1650
01:33:19,552 --> 01:33:21,388
The right move here is to move on

1651
01:33:23,623 --> 01:33:24,924
Marcula!

1652
01:33:25,058 --> 01:33:31,664
This is United States Destroyer
Joseph P. Kennedy!

1653
01:33:33,266 --> 01:33:34,467
This is point
at which we are concemed...

1654
01:33:34,567 --> 01:33:38,571
that there might be shooting
among the ships at sea

1655
01:33:38,571 --> 01:33:41,875
with the possibility that invasion
might have to be undertaken

1656
01:33:41,875 --> 01:33:45,445
to assure that
those bases are eliminated

1657
01:33:45,612 --> 01:33:47,814
If invasion is undertaken
the Russians have said

1658
01:33:47,947 --> 01:33:51,484
that they would
retaliate with rocket fire

1659
01:33:51,618 --> 01:33:53,420
We have said
if there's rocket fire from Cuba

1660
01:33:53,486 --> 01:33:57,524
we will retaliate
And there goes the whole ballgame

1661
01:33:57,624 --> 01:33:58,992
Kenny

1662
01:33:59,092 --> 01:34:00,660
What's this?

1663
01:34:00,760 --> 01:34:02,328
Can anyone just walk in here now?

1664
01:34:02,429 --> 01:34:03,963
Ken, don't worry
I'm not here to do an interview

1665
01:34:04,097 --> 01:34:06,166
If you're looking for a cup of sugar
John, you got the wrong door

1666
01:34:06,232 --> 01:34:07,467
Kenny

1667
01:34:07,567 --> 01:34:09,169
we need to see the President

1668
01:34:09,269 --> 01:34:10,737
Something's happened

1669
01:34:12,939 --> 01:34:15,742
I have lunch with him
Maybe once a month

1670
01:34:15,842 --> 01:34:18,244
Way the talks, he acts like
he knows Kruschev personally

1671
01:34:18,344 --> 01:34:20,180
but he's never elaborated

1672
01:34:20,880 --> 01:34:23,249
I've used him as a source
in a couple of stories

1673
01:34:23,383 --> 01:34:28,021
The FBI has identified
this Alexander Fomin as the...

1674
01:34:28,088 --> 01:34:30,990
Soviet Rezident, the KGB equivalent
of one of our station chiefs

1675
01:34:31,057 --> 01:34:34,160
He's their highest ranking spy
in this country

1676
01:34:34,227 --> 01:34:35,428
And he knows John's a friend of mine

1677
01:34:35,562 --> 01:34:37,864
All the trademarks of
a back-channel overture

1678
01:34:37,931 --> 01:34:40,667
Yeah. Some back channel

1679
01:34:40,734 --> 01:34:44,037
ABC News guy
My goddamn next-door neighbor

1680
01:34:46,272 --> 01:34:48,208
So they'll remove the missiles

1681
01:34:48,274 --> 01:34:51,010
And we'll pledge not to
invade Cuba or de-stabilize Castro

1682
01:34:51,111 --> 01:34:53,380
or assist anyone who plans on doing so

1683
01:34:57,283 --> 01:35:00,520
I think this may be
our first real message from Kruschev

1684
01:35:00,587 --> 01:35:01,888
The alternative, Mr. President

1685
01:35:02,021 --> 01:35:04,858
is that is this could be a trap

1686
01:35:05,358 --> 01:35:06,760
And how is that exactly?

1687
01:35:06,860 --> 01:35:08,428
Dangle a settlement

1688
01:35:08,561 --> 01:35:11,264
tie us down in negotiations
we come up short

1689
01:35:11,931 --> 01:35:14,300
Why else would they
approach us this way?

1690
01:35:14,401 --> 01:35:15,835
It's deniable

1691
01:35:15,935 --> 01:35:16,870
The Soviets have done nothing
but lie to us

1692
01:35:16,936 --> 01:35:18,772
This could just be more of the same

1693
01:35:18,838 --> 01:35:21,641
That may be
why Kruschev's introducing this guy

1694
01:35:22,042 --> 01:35:24,778
We're been burned by his usual players
in the formal channels

1695
01:35:24,878 --> 01:35:27,414
so he brings in an honest broker

1696
01:35:27,480 --> 01:35:29,582
That may be what they want us to think

1697
01:35:29,949 --> 01:35:30,917
The truth is

1698
01:35:31,017 --> 01:35:33,820
we don't really know
who Fomin speaks for

1699
01:35:33,953 --> 01:35:35,055
It could be Kruschev

1700
01:35:35,155 --> 01:35:37,090
It could be some faction
in the Politburo

1701
01:35:37,223 --> 01:35:38,758
Or the KGB itself

1702
01:35:38,825 --> 01:35:40,026
We just don't know

1703
01:35:40,493 --> 01:35:43,863
By the way, Scali
your activities now fall under...

1704
01:35:43,963 --> 01:35:45,765
the secrecy codicils
of the National Security Act

1705
01:35:45,899 --> 01:35:47,300
Sorry, John

1706
01:35:47,367 --> 01:35:49,035
No Pulitzer

1707
01:35:50,370 --> 01:35:52,772
Mr. President, we haven't much time

1708
01:35:52,872 --> 01:35:55,575
I'm scheduled to meet with him again
in three and a half hours

1709
01:35:55,709 --> 01:35:57,777
So it seems the question of the day is

1710
01:35:57,844 --> 01:35:59,546
is the offer legitimate?

1711
01:36:00,380 --> 01:36:02,048
And if it is

1712
01:36:02,115 --> 01:36:04,818
we can't afford to ignore it

1713
01:36:05,685 --> 01:36:07,987
So, John...

1714
01:36:08,488 --> 01:36:11,991
We'll have instructions for you
in a couple of hours

1715
01:36:12,125 --> 01:36:13,460
Thank you

1716
01:36:15,295 --> 01:36:16,730
Thank you

1717
01:36:18,598 --> 01:36:22,435
We don't have much time
to play out back-channe

1718
01:36:26,639 --> 01:36:29,075
Kenny

1719
01:36:30,410 --> 01:36:32,479
I want you to get over
to your old stomping grounds...

1720
01:36:32,545 --> 01:36:35,281
and go through everything
the FBI has on Fomin

1721
01:36:35,382 --> 01:36:37,450
I need your best call
Is the guy legit

1722
01:36:37,517 --> 01:36:39,419
and is he speaking for Kruschev?

1723
01:36:39,886 --> 01:36:40,954
So what we've got here is this guy

1724
01:36:41,087 --> 01:36:44,157
Alexander Feklisov
AKA Alexander Fomin

1725
01:36:44,224 --> 01:36:46,926
delclared Consul to the Soviet Embassy

1726
01:36:47,093 --> 01:36:49,095
but in reality the KGB Papa Spy

1727
01:36:49,863 --> 01:36:52,432
An illustrious tour of duty
during the Great Patriotic War

1728
01:36:52,532 --> 01:36:54,801
gets him on the Party fast track

1729
01:36:54,901 --> 01:36:59,706
Various tours of duty in KGB
American postings

1730
01:36:59,773 --> 01:37:01,141
He's an expert on us

1731
01:37:01,207 --> 01:37:03,777
And that is all we got on Papa Spy

1732
01:37:06,913 --> 01:37:10,050
How do you become the KGB top spy
in the United States?

1733
01:37:10,116 --> 01:37:12,152
Gotta know someone

1734
01:37:12,552 --> 01:37:13,853
You gotta know someone

1735
01:37:15,722 --> 01:37:17,624
So politics is politics

1736
01:37:29,469 --> 01:37:32,272
Walter, get me Kruschev's files

1737
01:37:32,338 --> 01:37:32,939
Pass me that

1738
01:37:33,039 --> 01:37:37,243
I wanna see their career
chronologies side by side

1739
01:37:37,310 --> 01:37:39,045
We know they're not related, right?

1740
01:37:39,145 --> 01:37:39,746
Right

1741
01:37:39,846 --> 01:37:42,082
They're not from the same hometown

1742
01:37:42,148 --> 01:37:43,450
They went to different schools

1743
01:37:43,583 --> 01:37:45,452
Right

1744
01:37:45,552 --> 01:37:47,787
So if they were gonna meet

1745
01:37:47,854 --> 01:37:49,823
they should have met here

1746
01:37:49,956 --> 01:37:50,824
I think they could've met

1747
01:37:50,924 --> 01:37:52,492
They could not

1748
01:37:52,625 --> 01:37:54,661
He was an engineer
stationed outside of Moscow

1749
01:37:54,728 --> 01:37:56,629
at the end of '41

1750
01:37:57,864 --> 01:37:59,499
That's it

1751
01:38:00,033 --> 01:38:01,434
They know each other

1752
01:38:02,035 --> 01:38:02,902
They're war buddies

1753
01:38:03,036 --> 01:38:04,504
That's pretty thin, Kenny

1754
01:38:04,637 --> 01:38:06,840
Real life usually is, Walter

1755
01:38:08,808 --> 01:38:10,577
They know each other, Jack

1756
01:38:10,643 --> 01:38:12,545
Kruschev and Fomin were war buddies

1757
01:38:12,612 --> 01:38:13,513
You sure?

1758
01:38:13,613 --> 01:38:16,583
Don't take it to court, but we've
got good circumstantial evidenct

1759
01:38:16,716 --> 01:38:22,389
What's your instinct?
I gotta move on this

1760
01:38:22,455 --> 01:38:23,690
My gut's telling me that

1761
01:38:23,823 --> 01:38:28,695
Kruschev's tuming to a trusted
old friend to carry his message

1762
01:38:28,828 --> 01:38:30,930
Okay. We're going

1763
01:38:32,499 --> 01:38:33,767
I've been instructed to tell you

1764
01:38:33,900 --> 01:38:36,202
that the American government
would respond favorably

1765
01:38:36,302 --> 01:38:38,972
to an offer along the lines
that you have discussed

1766
01:38:39,372 --> 01:38:42,509
If such a solution were raised
at the U. N. by Ambassador Zorin

1767
01:38:42,542 --> 01:38:45,478
he would find a favorable reply
from Ambassador Stevenson

1768
01:38:46,146 --> 01:38:49,449
So I understand you correctly

1769
01:38:49,616 --> 01:38:52,986
if the missiles in Cuba
were dismantled

1770
01:38:53,086 --> 01:38:55,188
returned to the Soviet Union

1771
01:38:55,355 --> 01:38:57,724
and a guarantee was made
not to reintroduce them

1772
01:38:57,857 --> 01:38:59,692
the United States
would be prepared to guarantee

1773
01:38:59,759 --> 01:39:02,695
that it would never invade Cuba

1774
01:39:02,829 --> 01:39:04,631
That is correct

1775
01:39:04,731 --> 01:39:06,166
And this is from
the Highest Authority?

1776
01:39:06,232 --> 01:39:08,101
Yes. The Highest Authority

1777
01:39:09,402 --> 01:39:11,004
There are two conditions

1778
01:39:11,071 --> 01:39:14,708
The U. N. must be allowed to
inspect the removal of the missiles

1779
01:39:15,208 --> 01:39:17,777
Of course the U. N.
must also be allowed to observe

1780
01:39:17,911 --> 01:39:20,313
the re-deployment of forces
from the American Southeast

1781
01:39:20,447 --> 01:39:21,781
I can't speak to that

1782
01:39:23,416 --> 01:39:25,585
What's the second condition?

1783
01:39:25,618 --> 01:39:27,220
Time is of the essence

1784
01:39:27,320 --> 01:39:28,288
How much time?

1785
01:39:28,421 --> 01:39:29,756
48 hours

1786
01:39:29,889 --> 01:39:33,026
In 48 hours, there can be no deals

1787
01:39:36,229 --> 01:39:37,297
I'll see what I can do

1788
01:39:54,247 --> 01:39:56,816
I think it's very difficult
to make a decision from this document

1789
01:39:56,883 --> 01:39:59,185
It looks to me like
Fomin's overture was genuine

1790
01:39:59,319 --> 01:40:00,553
It's a big "if", Bobby

1791
01:40:00,720 --> 01:40:02,322
It's ten pages of sentimental fluff

1792
01:40:02,455 --> 01:40:03,957
but he's saying it right here

1793
01:40:03,990 --> 01:40:07,660
He'll remove the missiles
in return for a no-invasion pledge

1794
01:40:07,727 --> 01:40:10,830
Mr. President, our early analysis
says this probably...

1795
01:40:10,897 --> 01:40:12,465
was written by Kruschev himself
It's a first draft

1796
01:40:12,932 --> 01:40:14,401
It shows no signs of being polished
by the foreign ministry

1797
01:40:14,501 --> 01:40:16,469
It probably wasn't
even approved by the Politburo

1798
01:40:16,536 --> 01:40:21,374
as they wouldn't
let the emotionalism go by

1799
01:40:21,474 --> 01:40:25,578
The analysts say it was written
by someone under considerable stress

1800
01:40:26,346 --> 01:40:28,281
Glad to know we're not alone

1801
01:40:31,251 --> 01:40:34,521
It never was my intention
to invade Cuba anyway

1802
01:40:34,587 --> 01:40:37,057
till they put the missiles in there

1803
01:40:38,425 --> 01:40:42,662
Gentlemen, I think we should
seriously consider this deal

1804
01:41:15,128 --> 01:41:15,962
Hi

1805
01:41:16,062 --> 01:41:17,530
Hi

1806
01:41:17,997 --> 01:41:20,033
You look old, O'Donnell

1807
01:41:20,967 --> 01:41:22,869
You don't

1808
01:41:23,002 --> 01:41:28,908
It's 2:30 in the morning
You flirting with me?

1809
01:41:28,975 --> 01:41:31,845
We got a back-channel communication

1810
01:41:32,011 --> 01:41:36,182
form Kruschev this evening
feeling us out about a deal

1811
01:41:36,282 --> 01:41:38,385
He confirmed it
just a little while ago in a letter

1812
01:41:38,518 --> 01:41:40,387
Thank God

1813
01:41:40,487 --> 01:41:44,257
Jack kicked us out of his house
for the night

1814
01:41:44,691 --> 01:41:46,526
Darn it

1815
01:41:46,626 --> 01:41:49,095
For a second there
I thought you'd been fired

1816
01:41:49,229 --> 01:41:51,164
No such luck

1817
01:41:57,237 --> 01:41:59,572
Driving home

1818
01:42:00,840 --> 01:42:04,277
there was something
I wanted to tell you

1819
01:42:10,683 --> 01:42:12,719
Finish that thought

1820
01:42:16,389 --> 01:42:16,956
Yes?

1821
01:42:17,090 --> 01:42:17,957
Kenny, It's Bob

1822
01:42:18,024 --> 01:42:20,527
We're getting another letter
over the teletype from Kruschev

1823
01:42:20,627 --> 01:42:21,394
I have a bad feeling

1824
01:42:21,528 --> 01:42:22,996
I'll be right there

1825
01:42:29,903 --> 01:42:31,237
You're beautiful

1826
01:42:37,677 --> 01:42:39,746
It looks like
Fomin was a ploy after all

1827
01:42:39,813 --> 01:42:41,448
and they were just stalling for time

1828
01:42:48,621 --> 01:42:50,390
It gets worse

1829
01:42:51,124 --> 01:42:52,025
Gentlemen

1830
01:42:52,125 --> 01:42:54,194
my specialists are in agreement

1831
01:42:54,728 --> 01:42:56,463
This morning's letter is not Kruschev
Last night's letter was

1832
01:42:56,596 --> 01:42:58,064
The evidence supports
only one conclusion

1833
01:42:58,665 --> 01:43:03,770
There's been a coup
and Kruschev was replaced overnight

1834
01:43:04,304 --> 01:43:05,205
Dean?

1835
01:43:05,338 --> 01:43:08,775
It does suggest he's been co-opted
by hard-line elements

1836
01:43:08,908 --> 01:43:11,144
Which at the end of the day
amounts to the same thing

1837
01:43:11,277 --> 01:43:12,412
A puppet Kruschev

1838
01:43:12,545 --> 01:43:14,981
and a hard-line Soviet government
pulling the strings

1839
01:43:15,048 --> 01:43:18,451
No deal. And the missiles
are almost operational

1840
01:43:18,485 --> 01:43:21,154
What if the Soviets have no intention
of honoring this second deal?

1841
01:43:21,254 --> 01:43:23,189
The tomorrow
they make another condition

1842
01:43:23,289 --> 01:43:25,825
Meanwhile
the quarantine isn't working

1843
01:43:25,925 --> 01:43:28,395
and they're completing work
on the missiles sites

1844
01:43:29,162 --> 01:43:32,532
Sir, I think we have to issue
pre- invasion orders for our forces

1845
01:43:33,033 --> 01:43:34,601
Mr. President

1846
01:43:34,701 --> 01:43:36,469
This morning's photography is in

1847
01:43:37,037 --> 01:43:41,274
It appears the Soviet have commenced a
crash program to ready their missiles

1848
01:43:41,408 --> 01:43:44,210
The first missiles
become operational last night

1849
01:43:44,611 --> 01:43:47,147
We expect they'll all be operational
in 36 hours

1850
01:43:47,280 --> 01:43:48,581
Then we're out of time

1851
01:43:48,648 --> 01:43:49,382
We have to go in

1852
01:43:49,449 --> 01:43:51,351
That may not be
as easy as we thought, either

1853
01:43:51,518 --> 01:43:54,954
We have confirmation
the Soviets have also deployed

1854
01:43:55,088 --> 01:43:56,222
battlefield nuclear weapons to Cuba

1855
01:43:56,356 --> 01:43:57,490
FROGS, we call them

1856
01:43:57,590 --> 01:43:59,726
Short- range tactical nukes

1857
01:43:59,793 --> 01:44:02,462
We don't know whether
they've delegated release authority

1858
01:44:02,595 --> 01:44:05,665
to their local commanders
for use on our invasion troops

1859
01:44:05,799 --> 01:44:08,068
But the good news is
as of this moment

1860
01:44:08,134 --> 01:44:10,704
we know where the FROGS are
and we can target them, too

1861
01:44:11,938 --> 01:44:15,508
But the longer we wait
the harder it's going to get

1862
01:44:31,057 --> 01:44:32,792
We have no choice

1863
01:44:37,230 --> 01:44:39,232
General, issue orders to our forces

1864
01:44:39,366 --> 01:44:41,935
to be prepared to execute
the air strikes Monday morning

1865
01:44:43,136 --> 01:44:46,306
and the follow-on invasion
according to the schedule thereafter

1866
01:44:47,240 --> 01:44:50,143
I'll need the official release orders
on my desk Sunday night

1867
01:44:50,310 --> 01:44:51,745
Understood, sir

1868
01:44:52,212 --> 01:44:54,013
We need to step up our over flights

1869
01:44:54,114 --> 01:44:58,251
finalize our pilots' target folders
in order to carry out the strikes

1870
01:44:59,285 --> 01:45:00,286
Permission granted

1871
01:45:00,387 --> 01:45:01,488
Yes, sir

1872
01:45:11,865 --> 01:45:12,966
Gentlemen

1873
01:45:13,400 --> 01:45:16,336
if anybody's got any great ideas
now's the time

1874
01:45:24,711 --> 01:45:26,613
Major Anderson
there's a phone call for you

1875
01:45:26,713 --> 01:45:28,581
Thank you

1876
01:45:28,915 --> 01:45:30,583
Gimme just a second here, guys

1877
01:45:34,054 --> 01:45:35,555
This is Major Anderson

1878
01:45:37,290 --> 01:45:39,259
Hello? Anyone there?

1879
01:45:39,359 --> 01:45:39,859
Major?

1880
01:45:39,993 --> 01:45:41,194
Yes, sir

1881
01:45:41,294 --> 01:45:45,632
My name's Kenneth O'Donnell
Special Assistant to the President

1882
01:45:45,699 --> 01:45:48,201
Major, a few days ago
the President ordered me to...

1883
01:45:48,368 --> 01:45:51,104
help him keep control of
what's going on out there

1884
01:45:51,604 --> 01:45:56,676
I've been brow-beating pilots
navy guys left and right

1885
01:45:56,776 --> 01:46:00,380
to make sure you don't get us here
in Washington into trouble

1886
01:46:00,547 --> 01:46:02,949
But you know what?

1887
01:46:03,349 --> 01:46:06,653
We're pretty damn good ourselves
at getting into trouble

1888
01:46:06,720 --> 01:46:09,289
So instead of riding your ass

1889
01:46:09,756 --> 01:46:11,224
I'm just gonna tell you
what's going on here

1890
01:46:11,324 --> 01:46:13,159
and let you figure out
how best to help us out up here

1891
01:46:13,293 --> 01:46:14,894
Go ahead, sir

1892
01:46:15,528 --> 01:46:17,564
Last night, it looked like

1893
01:46:17,664 --> 01:46:20,367
we were gonna cut a deal
to get us all out of this mess

1894
01:46:20,834 --> 01:46:23,803
Today the Soviets are reneging

1895
01:46:23,870 --> 01:46:25,572
We're gonna try
and salvage the situation

1896
01:46:25,705 --> 01:46:30,009
but a lot of things
are going wrong today

1897
01:46:30,143 --> 01:46:32,679
It's making everyone nervous

1898
01:46:32,812 --> 01:46:35,515
If more things go wrong
people will become more nervous

1899
01:46:35,615 --> 01:46:39,119
and it will be very hard
to aviod going to war

1900
01:46:40,520 --> 01:46:42,789
I'm not sure
what you're trying to tell me, sir

1901
01:46:42,956 --> 01:46:44,224
Just my standard line

1902
01:46:44,357 --> 01:46:48,395
I've been repeating
to guys like you all week

1903
01:46:48,828 --> 01:46:50,630
Don't get shot down

1904
01:46:52,532 --> 01:46:53,466
Beyond that

1905
01:46:53,633 --> 01:46:56,236
whatever else you can do to help us
I'd appreciate it

1906
01:46:56,369 --> 01:46:58,271
Sir

1907
01:47:00,640 --> 01:47:05,779
When you're at 72, 000 feet
a million things can go wrong

1908
01:47:05,845 --> 01:47:09,616
Is your Oxygen mix right?
Are your cameras gonna freeze up?

1909
01:47:09,749 --> 01:47:10,717
Are you leaving a contrail?

1910
01:47:10,850 --> 01:47:13,753
Those million things
they're beyond your control, mostly

1911
01:47:13,820 --> 01:47:16,589
But...

1912
01:47:16,690 --> 01:47:19,159
when you realize that

1913
01:47:19,225 --> 01:47:21,061
there's a kind of peace

1914
01:47:21,127 --> 01:47:23,830
If you're a good man
and if your ground crew are good men

1915
01:47:23,897 --> 01:47:25,665
that is all you can ask for

1916
01:47:25,765 --> 01:47:28,668
And with the grace of God
that'll get you through

1917
01:47:29,135 --> 01:47:30,970
Are you a religious man?

1918
01:47:31,037 --> 01:47:32,472
I am

1919
01:47:34,808 --> 01:47:36,042
Good

1920
01:49:54,748 --> 01:49:56,549
The plane is missing, Kenny

1921
01:49:57,183 --> 01:49:59,552
We are presuming the pilot is dead

1922
01:50:12,032 --> 01:50:16,036
It's hard to believe with the Soviet
centralized command structure

1923
01:50:16,136 --> 01:50:17,971
that this could have been
an accidental launch

1924
01:50:18,104 --> 01:50:19,873
The question is, does this
attack on our plane represent

1925
01:50:20,040 --> 01:50:23,676
a definitive intentional escalation
on the part of the Soviets?

1926
01:50:23,810 --> 01:50:25,245
Mr. President

1927
01:50:25,311 --> 01:50:27,680
taken with the events
of the past few hours

1928
01:50:27,814 --> 01:50:30,083
I believe
this confirms our worst fears

1929
01:50:30,183 --> 01:50:32,585
We're now dealing with
a hard-line Soviet government

1930
01:50:32,652 --> 01:50:34,688
perhaps with Kruschev
as a puppet head, perhaps not

1931
01:50:34,821 --> 01:50:35,955
You okay?

1932
01:50:36,056 --> 01:50:37,557
Yeah

1933
01:50:38,191 --> 01:50:39,325
I'm fine

1934
01:50:41,261 --> 01:50:42,262
Mr. President

1935
01:50:42,896 --> 01:50:43,797
What now?

1936
01:50:43,930 --> 01:50:46,533
A U-2 on a routine
air- sampling mission got lost

1937
01:50:46,633 --> 01:50:48,401
and penetrated
Soviet airspace over Siberia

1938
01:50:48,468 --> 01:50:49,703
Oh, goddammit

1939
01:50:49,803 --> 01:50:52,505
The Soviets scrambled MIG's in pursuit
thinking it was a bomber

1940
01:50:52,605 --> 01:50:53,773
It got out okay

1941
01:50:53,873 --> 01:50:55,275
Somebody forgot to cancel the mission

1942
01:50:55,375 --> 01:50:57,977
There's always some sonofabitch
who doesn't get the word!

1943
01:50:58,078 --> 01:50:59,879
This is just what we need

1944
01:51:00,413 --> 01:51:02,248
the Soviets thinking
we're bombing them

1945
01:51:06,152 --> 01:51:07,420
Anybody else?

1946
01:51:07,520 --> 01:51:08,855
Mr. President

1947
01:51:08,988 --> 01:51:11,024
our pilots are in danger

1948
01:51:11,057 --> 01:51:14,894
We must order punitive air strikes
against the SAM site

1949
01:51:14,994 --> 01:51:17,697
that shot down Major Anderson
per our rules of engagement

1950
01:51:32,812 --> 01:51:34,147
No

1951
01:51:35,348 --> 01:51:37,684
I want confirmation
it wasn't some sort of accident first

1952
01:51:37,751 --> 01:51:38,284
Mr. President

1953
01:51:38,418 --> 01:51:42,555
Good idea, Mr. President
I can wait a day and half

1954
01:51:42,689 --> 01:51:45,325
Be safer for my boys
to get the SAM's on Monday

1955
01:51:45,425 --> 01:51:47,160
when we get the rest of the bastards

1956
01:53:34,534 --> 01:53:36,069
That's the quarter!

1957
01:53:42,342 --> 01:53:42,776
Hey, Dad

1958
01:53:42,876 --> 01:53:44,144
Hey, Sport

1959
01:53:44,244 --> 01:53:45,278
You winning?

1960
01:53:45,412 --> 01:53:46,946
Yeah

1961
01:53:47,514 --> 01:53:49,516
Is everything gonna be okay, Dad?

1962
01:53:51,718 --> 01:53:53,787
Everything's gonna be fine, Kenny

1963
01:53:55,155 --> 01:53:59,159
I guess
you won't be coming home tonight?

1964
01:54:01,628 --> 01:54:04,097
I...

1965
01:54:07,233 --> 01:54:10,503
Let's got! Second quarter!

1966
01:54:13,339 --> 01:54:15,675
It's okay. Go on back to your game

1967
01:54:16,076 --> 01:54:18,111
Alright. I'll see you around, Dad

1968
01:54:48,641 --> 01:54:49,709
Dammit!

1969
01:54:52,679 --> 01:54:53,813
Jesus, Mary and Joseph...

1970
01:54:53,913 --> 01:54:55,582
Take off for two hours
you're gonna miss a little drama

1971
01:54:55,715 --> 01:54:57,650
I told you how stupid it was
to float that Lippman article

1972
01:54:57,784 --> 01:54:59,452
Now you're gonna do it for real?

1973
01:54:59,552 --> 01:55:00,687
The Jupiters are obsolete, Kenny

1974
01:55:00,820 --> 01:55:02,188
They were supposed to
have been dismantled last summer

1975
01:55:02,288 --> 01:55:05,091
I know they're obsolete
That's not the point!

1976
01:55:05,525 --> 01:55:08,795
The point is you trade our missiles
in Turkey for theirs in Cuba

1977
01:55:08,962 --> 01:55:11,364
they're gonna force us into
trade after trade, until finally

1978
01:55:11,464 --> 01:55:14,200
a couple of months from now
they demand something we won't trade

1979
01:55:14,334 --> 01:55:15,635
like Berlin

1980
01:55:16,069 --> 01:55:17,704
And we do end up in a war

1981
01:55:18,304 --> 01:55:19,606
Not to mention that
long before that happens

1982
01:55:19,639 --> 01:55:21,708
this administration
will be politically dead

1983
01:55:21,808 --> 01:55:24,844
I don't care if this administration
ends up in the freaking toilet

1984
01:55:24,944 --> 01:55:26,980
We don't do a deal tonight
there won't be any administration

1985
01:55:27,080 --> 01:55:30,183
It's the wrong move, Bobby
and it's not just me who thinks that

1986
01:55:30,316 --> 01:55:33,953
Everyone on this so-called EXCOM's
telling you the same thing

1987
01:55:34,621 --> 01:55:36,923
Whose side are you on now, Ken?

1988
01:55:37,557 --> 01:55:39,893
Oh, goddammit

1989
01:55:41,428 --> 01:55:43,363
What if there
hasn't been a coup at all?

1990
01:55:45,098 --> 01:55:47,067
What if it's you two?

1991
01:55:47,434 --> 01:55:48,201
What is that supposed to mean?

1992
01:55:48,268 --> 01:55:50,003
What if it was you two

1993
01:55:50,103 --> 01:55:54,307
who invited that second letter by
raising the possibility of a trade?

1994
01:56:00,313 --> 01:56:02,782
Mr. President
we have only 30 hours left

1995
01:56:02,916 --> 01:56:04,150
and whatever response we send

1996
01:56:04,284 --> 01:56:06,553
it'll take several hours
to reach our embassy

1997
01:56:06,619 --> 01:56:09,522
and be delievered to the Kremlin

1998
01:56:09,622 --> 01:56:11,925
So early tomorrow morning
is the earliest

1999
01:56:12,058 --> 01:56:13,927
Kruschev could respond

2000
01:56:14,728 --> 01:56:17,297
Which one of you geniuses
is gonna tell me how to

2001
01:56:17,397 --> 01:56:19,599
explain it to the world
if we don't make this trade?

2002
01:56:20,734 --> 01:56:23,169
So what are we gonna say
to the Soviets

2003
01:56:23,269 --> 01:56:25,038
about this offer?

2004
01:56:25,138 --> 01:56:26,306
Well, it depends, doesn't it?

2005
01:56:26,406 --> 01:56:29,943
Do we really believe
there's been a coup?

2006
01:56:30,310 --> 01:56:31,978
What if Fomin wasn't a ploy?

2007
01:56:32,712 --> 01:56:34,514
What if his message was real?

2008
01:56:34,681 --> 01:56:37,951
What if what is happening
is a series of accidents?

2009
01:56:38,084 --> 01:56:41,054
Accidents like them
shooting down our U-2?

2010
01:56:42,355 --> 01:56:43,957
Yes. Accidents like that

2011
01:56:44,391 --> 01:56:46,960
And the accidents are making the
second letter seem more aggressive

2012
01:56:47,594 --> 01:56:51,097
and the whole situation
appear worse than it really is

2013
01:56:51,197 --> 01:56:52,098
"The Gun of August"

2014
01:56:52,165 --> 01:56:53,466
That's right

2015
01:56:53,900 --> 01:56:56,169
So we just reject the second letter?

2016
01:56:56,770 --> 01:56:57,470
No

2017
01:56:58,038 --> 01:56:59,239
We don't...

2018
01:56:59,305 --> 01:57:00,674
reject it

2019
01:57:00,774 --> 01:57:02,075
We accept the first letter

2020
01:57:02,175 --> 01:57:04,411
and pretend
the second one doesn't exist

2021
01:57:06,613 --> 01:57:08,748
It won't work
because that's wishful thinking

2022
01:57:08,882 --> 01:57:10,150
Look, he made an offer. So I...

2023
01:57:10,216 --> 01:57:12,152
The same wishful thinking, Bobby
that blinded us all these months

2024
01:57:12,318 --> 01:57:16,222
while the Soviets were sneaking
those missiles in under our noses

2025
01:57:16,356 --> 01:57:17,457
Ignore the second letter

2026
01:57:17,524 --> 01:57:18,958
agree to the conditions of the first

2027
01:57:19,059 --> 01:57:20,894
There is no reason to believe
the Soviets will let it go

2028
01:57:21,027 --> 01:57:23,329
Max is right. Why will they accept it?

2029
01:57:23,430 --> 01:57:24,698
It can work

2030
01:57:24,764 --> 01:57:28,201
If they believe
we're gonna hit 'em hard

2031
01:57:28,268 --> 01:57:31,404
We've got time for one more round
of diplomacy, and that's it

2032
01:57:31,504 --> 01:57:33,473
First airstrikes start in 28 hours

2033
01:57:33,540 --> 01:57:34,941
But we have to make them agree to it

2034
01:57:35,141 --> 01:57:36,343
So how do we do that?

2035
01:57:36,343 --> 01:57:37,711
We give them something

2036
01:57:37,844 --> 01:57:40,180
We tell them
we'll remove the missiles from Turkey

2037
01:57:40,180 --> 01:57:41,281
Hang on

2038
01:57:41,281 --> 01:57:44,951
But we don that six months from now
so it appears there's no linkage

2039
01:57:45,051 --> 01:57:47,420
We also tell them
if they go public about it

2040
01:57:47,554 --> 01:57:48,254
we'll deny it

2041
01:57:48,355 --> 01:57:49,456
Right we deny it. The deal's off

2042
01:57:49,589 --> 01:57:52,092
And we do it under the table
so we can disavow any knowledge of it

2043
01:57:52,225 --> 01:57:54,594
It's transparent, Kenny
The press will be all over it

2044
01:57:54,694 --> 01:57:57,630
Six months from now
we're not gonna care, are we?

2045
01:57:57,764 --> 01:57:58,498
We'll deal with it then

2046
01:57:58,631 --> 01:58:01,634
At the least, it'll expulse
whether Kruschev has been overthrown

2047
01:58:01,768 --> 01:58:03,002
We'll know who we're up against

2048
01:58:03,103 --> 01:58:04,704
I've been thinking about Kruschev

2049
01:58:04,804 --> 01:58:07,674
And if this is a move to appease
the hard-liners in his government

2050
01:58:07,841 --> 01:58:11,044
it may be just the bone he needs to
regain control of his own house

2051
01:58:11,111 --> 01:58:14,647
Whoever carries the message
has to hit the nail on the head

2052
01:58:14,748 --> 01:58:17,083
If we come across as too soft
they'll push us

2053
01:58:17,150 --> 01:58:20,720
Too hard, they'll be cornered
and even more dangerous

2054
01:58:20,854 --> 01:58:22,756
All of you do understand

2055
01:58:22,856 --> 01:58:25,625
that there is an enormous risk
in offering this deal

2056
01:58:25,759 --> 01:58:27,961
Because if they turn us down
and we've already told them

2057
01:58:28,028 --> 01:58:29,229
that we're coming in on Monday morning

2058
01:58:29,329 --> 01:58:30,196
They'll strike first

2059
01:58:30,296 --> 01:58:31,398
Yes

2060
01:58:34,601 --> 01:58:35,735
Bobby

2061
01:58:36,302 --> 01:58:38,471
You know Dobrynin best

2062
01:58:38,571 --> 01:58:40,840
Yeah

2063
01:58:40,940 --> 01:58:42,375
Then you're it

2064
01:58:44,010 --> 01:58:46,012
Ted, I want you
to start working the draft

2065
01:58:46,446 --> 01:58:49,249
Bobby, you gotta go in there
and make them understand

2066
01:58:49,416 --> 01:58:51,317
that we have to
have an answer tomorrow

2067
01:58:51,384 --> 01:58:53,620
Because Monday we go to war

2068
01:59:10,470 --> 01:59:12,906
What do you want, a goodbye kiss?

2069
01:59:15,775 --> 01:59:17,210
Listen

2070
01:59:17,344 --> 01:59:18,445
I'll take care of him

2071
01:59:18,578 --> 01:59:20,747
Go on inside, grab some coffee
We'll be back pretty quick

2072
01:59:20,847 --> 01:59:21,448
Are you sure?

2073
01:59:21,548 --> 01:59:22,282
Sure

2074
01:59:22,382 --> 01:59:23,983
What's the matter with you?

2075
01:59:24,050 --> 01:59:25,952
Forget how to open a car door?

2076
01:59:28,588 --> 01:59:30,523
Jesus!

2077
01:59:30,590 --> 01:59:32,292
You rich people

2078
01:59:40,834 --> 01:59:44,437
I promised the girls
I'd take them riding tomorrow

2079
01:59:46,106 --> 01:59:49,042
Make sure you keep that date

2080
01:59:51,311 --> 01:59:56,049
We gave up so much to get here

2081
01:59:56,149 --> 01:59:58,318
Sometimes I think
"What the hell did we do it for? "

2082
01:59:58,918 --> 01:59:59,986
I don't know about you

2083
02:00:00,120 --> 02:00:02,922
but I'm in it for the money

2084
02:00:08,795 --> 02:00:12,332
We knew we could do a better job
than everyone else

2085
02:00:12,465 --> 02:00:13,800
Remember?

2086
02:00:14,768 --> 02:00:16,469
You know, I...

2087
02:00:16,603 --> 02:00:21,608
I hate being called the brilliant one

2088
02:00:21,741 --> 02:00:23,743
The ruthless one

2089
02:00:24,210 --> 02:00:26,646
The guy everybody's afraid of

2090
02:00:26,746 --> 02:00:28,181
I hate it

2091
02:00:29,482 --> 02:00:31,384
I'm not so smart

2092
02:00:32,786 --> 02:00:34,254
I'm not so ruthless

2093
02:00:34,688 --> 02:00:37,257
Well, you're right
about the smart part

2094
02:00:46,733 --> 02:00:48,835
I don't know if I can do this

2095
02:00:49,903 --> 02:00:52,472
There's nobody else I'd rather
have going in there than you

2096
02:00:52,605 --> 02:00:56,176
Nobody else I trust

2097
02:00:56,309 --> 02:00:58,244
Helen and the kids' lives to

2098
02:01:00,613 --> 02:01:01,948
Take a left

2099
02:01:21,101 --> 02:01:22,435
You smell that?

2100
02:01:22,969 --> 02:01:24,537
They're burning their documents

2101
02:01:25,972 --> 02:01:27,507
They think we're going to war

2102
02:01:30,310 --> 02:01:32,012
God help us, Ken

2103
02:02:13,319 --> 02:02:16,256
Sir, Ambassador Dobrynin is here
He's in your office

2104
02:02:27,367 --> 02:02:29,302
I'll whistle up some luck for you

2105
02:02:37,911 --> 02:02:39,212
Mr. Ambassador

2106
02:02:39,312 --> 02:02:40,613
Thank you for coming

2107
02:03:30,797 --> 02:03:32,399
Who are you?

2108
02:03:42,776 --> 02:03:44,344
The friend

2109
02:04:05,165 --> 02:04:08,368
My brother, my friends
my countrymen, and I

2110
02:04:08,501 --> 02:04:11,504
cannot and will not permit
those missiles to become operational

2111
02:04:11,638 --> 02:04:12,872
I promise you that

2112
02:04:12,906 --> 02:04:16,476
Then I fear our two nations
will go to war

2113
02:04:16,609 --> 02:04:18,945
And I fear where war will lead us

2114
02:04:19,045 --> 02:04:21,881
If the missiles
do not become operational

2115
02:04:21,948 --> 02:04:25,352
if you remove them
there will be no war

2116
02:04:26,686 --> 02:04:28,955
At this moment, the President
is accepting the terms of

2117
02:04:29,089 --> 02:04:31,558
Secretary Kruschev's letter
of Friday night

2118
02:04:32,025 --> 02:04:34,427
If the Soviet Union
halts construction immediately

2119
02:04:34,494 --> 02:04:37,464
removes the missiles
and submits to U. N. inspection

2120
02:04:37,530 --> 02:04:40,734
the United States
will pledge to never invade Cuba

2121
02:04:40,800 --> 02:04:42,969
or aid others in that enterprise

2122
02:04:43,069 --> 02:04:46,106
If you Jupiter missiles in Turkey
were removed also

2123
02:04:46,206 --> 02:04:48,908
such an accommodation could be reached

2124
02:04:49,242 --> 02:04:50,643
That's not possible

2125
02:04:53,747 --> 02:04:57,250
The United States cannot agree
to such terms under threat

2126
02:04:58,084 --> 02:05:01,421
Any belief to the contrary
was in error

2127
02:05:02,455 --> 02:05:04,691
You want war?

2128
02:05:14,234 --> 02:05:15,468
However

2129
02:05:15,502 --> 02:05:18,505
While there can be no quid pro
on this issue

2130
02:05:18,605 --> 02:05:21,841
the United States
can offer a private assurance

2131
02:05:23,443 --> 02:05:25,979
Our Jupiter missiles in Turkey
are obsolete

2132
02:05:26,146 --> 02:05:29,015
and have been scheduled
for withdrawal for some time

2133
02:05:29,082 --> 02:05:32,986
This withdrawal should take place
within six months

2134
02:05:33,687 --> 02:05:36,022
Of course, any public disclosure
of this assurance

2135
02:05:36,122 --> 02:05:39,492
would negate the deal and produce...

2136
02:05:39,626 --> 02:05:41,695
the most stringent denials
from our government

2137
02:05:41,828 --> 02:05:43,730
This private assurance...

2138
02:05:43,863 --> 02:05:47,300
represents the word
of the Highest Authority?

2139
02:05:47,400 --> 02:05:49,336
Yes

2140
02:05:49,402 --> 02:05:52,405
And it can be relayed
beyond Comrade Krushcev's ears

2141
02:05:52,539 --> 02:05:54,441
to the top circles of my government?

2142
02:05:54,507 --> 02:05:58,278
Our pledge can be relayed to
any government officials

2143
02:05:58,378 --> 02:06:00,046
Secretary Kruschev sees fit to satisfy

2144
02:06:00,513 --> 02:06:01,414
With the caveat that...

2145
02:06:01,514 --> 02:06:05,385
it is not to be made public
in any way, shape or form

2146
02:06:09,489 --> 02:06:13,426
And we must have an answer tomorrow
at the latest

2147
02:06:13,526 --> 02:06:15,895
I cannot stress this point enough

2148
02:06:15,996 --> 02:06:17,130
Tomorrow?

2149
02:06:18,832 --> 02:06:19,899
Tomorrow

2150
02:06:22,002 --> 02:06:24,004
Then you must excuse me
and permit me to relay...

2151
02:06:24,070 --> 02:06:27,474
the substance of our discussion
to my superiors

2152
02:06:27,607 --> 02:06:29,075
Of course

2153
02:06:31,111 --> 02:06:35,148
We've heard stories that
some of your military men wish for war

2154
02:06:36,616 --> 02:06:38,485
You are a good man

2155
02:06:38,618 --> 02:06:40,387
Your brother is a good man

2156
02:06:40,453 --> 02:06:43,390
I assure you there are other good men

2157
02:06:43,523 --> 02:06:45,058
Let us hope the will of good men
is enough to counter

2158
02:06:45,225 --> 02:06:49,796
the terrible strength of this thing
that was put in motion

2159
02:07:29,903 --> 02:07:31,871
What's going to happen?

2160
02:07:34,741 --> 02:07:38,345
If the sun comes up tomorrow

2161
02:07:38,478 --> 02:07:41,014
it is only because of men of good will

2162
02:07:43,683 --> 02:07:45,785
And that's...

2163
02:07:45,852 --> 02:07:48,955
all there is between us and the Devil

2164
02:08:21,955 --> 02:08:24,658
This is Radio Moscow

2165
02:08:24,791 --> 02:08:26,259
Premier Kruschev...

2166
02:08:26,393 --> 02:08:29,663
has sent a message
to President Kennedy today

2167
02:08:29,763 --> 02:08:32,465
This message re-emphasizes

2168
02:08:32,565 --> 02:08:36,536
the need for urgent measures
to prevent a fatal turn of events

2169
02:08:36,636 --> 02:08:38,538
and to preserve world peace

2170
02:08:39,205 --> 02:08:42,008
In addition to
instructions earlier transmitted

2171
02:08:42,108 --> 02:08:45,011
to stop construction work
on installations in Cuba

2172
02:08:45,178 --> 02:08:49,249
the Soviet government has ordered
the dismantling of weapons in Cuba

2173
02:08:49,349 --> 02:08:53,019
as well as their crating
and return to the Soviet Union

2174
02:09:04,030 --> 02:09:05,965
Is everybody ready for church?

2175
02:09:13,973 --> 02:09:15,675
It's a beautiful morning

2176
02:09:19,646 --> 02:09:21,348
Pass the butter up to Dad

2177
02:09:26,586 --> 02:09:29,089
Dad, you want your paper?

2178
02:09:32,826 --> 02:09:34,561
Dad, what's wrong?

2179
02:09:39,065 --> 02:09:41,001
The sun came up

2180
02:09:42,569 --> 02:09:46,439
Every day the sun comes up
says something about us

2181
02:09:55,482 --> 02:09:57,584
What does it say, Dad?

2182
02:09:58,918 --> 02:10:01,421
What's wrong with Daddy?

2183
02:10:35,422 --> 02:10:38,425
This is the foreign policy trophy
we were hoping for

2184
02:10:42,329 --> 02:10:43,263
Mr. President

2185
02:10:43,363 --> 02:10:44,631
great job

2186
02:10:44,764 --> 02:10:46,866
Hold it

2187
02:10:46,966 --> 02:10:49,002
Well, Mr. President

2188
02:10:49,135 --> 02:10:51,304
I think I can speak for everyone here

2189
02:10:51,371 --> 02:10:53,873
when I say bring on those mid-terms

2190
02:10:54,007 --> 02:10:57,110
there's no stopping us now

2191
02:10:57,210 --> 02:10:59,646
Four more years! All right!

2192
02:10:59,746 --> 02:11:02,582
You know, it's been a long two weeks

2193
02:11:02,682 --> 02:11:03,883
Whatever

2194
02:11:04,017 --> 02:11:06,886
And I'd like to thank you all
I think you did a great job

2195
02:11:07,020 --> 02:11:11,458
I just don't think
we should be gloating too much

2196
02:11:13,059 --> 02:11:16,930
It was just as much a victory
for them as it was for us

2197
02:11:17,097 --> 02:11:18,531
Hear hear!

2198
02:11:18,698 --> 02:11:19,799
Enjoy your morning

2199
02:11:19,866 --> 02:11:21,468
Thank you, Mr. President

2200
02:11:24,037 --> 02:11:25,905
Get some rest, Mr. President

2201
02:11:26,840 --> 02:11:29,042
We've got a lot of new clout right now

2202
02:11:29,109 --> 02:11:30,477
We can run the table on Kruschev

2203
02:11:30,543 --> 02:11:31,845
the Middle East and Southeast Asia

2204
02:11:31,978 --> 02:11:33,680
You're right

2205
02:11:44,758 --> 02:11:47,894
Dear Mr. and Mrs. Anderson

2206
02:11:47,961 --> 02:11:51,898
I was deeply shocked
when advised your son was lost

2207
02:11:51,965 --> 02:11:56,503
in an operational mission on Saturday

2208
02:11:58,438 --> 02:12:00,140
October 27th, 1962

2209
02:12:00,273 --> 02:12:01,808
Your son rendered distinguished
and dedicated service to his country

2210
02:12:01,975 --> 02:12:03,843
throughout his career

2211
02:12:04,644 --> 02:12:08,648
He was admired

2212
02:12:08,748 --> 02:12:10,650
and respected for his courage

2213
02:12:10,750 --> 02:12:13,653
and his professional skill
by all with whom he served

2214
02:12:14,120 --> 02:12:16,890
His tragic loss will be deeply felt

2215
02:12:17,557 --> 02:12:19,793
and a grateful nation
will be forever in his debt

2216
02:12:40,947 --> 02:12:42,515
Ken! We're out here

2217
02:13:01,601 --> 02:13:04,070
What kind of a peace do we seek?

2218
02:13:04,170 --> 02:13:06,773
I am talking about genuine peace

2219
02:13:06,873 --> 02:13:09,909
The kind of peace that
makes life on earth worth living

2220
02:13:10,010 --> 02:13:12,012
Not merely peace in our time

2221
02:13:12,145 --> 02:13:14,381
but peace in all time

2222
02:13:14,547 --> 02:13:16,516
Our problems are man-made

2223
02:13:16,649 --> 02:13:19,486
therefor they can be solved by man

2224
02:13:19,586 --> 02:13:21,254
For in the final analysis

2225
02:13:21,321 --> 02:13:23,790
our most basic common link

2226
02:13:23,890 --> 02:13:27,794
is that we all
inhabit this small planet

2227
02:13:27,927 --> 02:13:30,063
We all breathe the same air

2228
02:13:30,163 --> 02:13:32,766
We all cherish our children's futures

